embeddableConfig.description: If the load balancer is unable to establish a connection, the load balancer stores one of the following reason codes in the connection log.

query.esql:
FROM logs-*
| WHERE data_stream.dataset == "aws.elb_logs"
| where aws.elb.leaf_client_cert_not_after < now() - 30days
| limit 10000
| stats COUNT_DISTINCT(aws.elb.leaf_client_cert_serial_number) by aws.elb.listener, aws.elb.ssl_protocol, aws.elb.leaf_client_cert_serial_number, aws.elb.leaf_client_cert_subject, aws.elb.leaf_client_cert_not_after
| keep aws.elb.listener, aws.elb.ssl_protocol, aws.elb.leaf_client_cert_serial_number, aws.elb.leaf_client_cert_subject, aws.elb.leaf_client_cert_not_after
| sort aws.elb.leaf_client_cert_not_after asc

panelsJSON.title: Certificate Expired or Expiring in 30 days
